    <!--                  SECTION THREE: SIMILAR POLYGONS & AREA         -->
    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDef_14">• Ratio of similitude (k) = corresponding side lengths ratio of similar polygons.</string>

    <!-- Q: Sides 9 and 3 — what is k? Answer: 3 -->
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefQuestion_14">Two similar polygons have corresponding sides of length 9 and 3. What is the ratio of similitude k?</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefAnswerOne_14">3</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefAnswerTwo_14">6</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefAnswerThree_14">27</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefCorrectAnswer_14">3</string>

    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryProperties_14">• Compute area by dividing polygons into triangles.
\n • Areas of similar polygons ratio = k².
\n • Convex quadrilateral area = ½ × product of diagonals × sinα.</string>

    <!-- Q: k=3 — what is the ratio of areas? Answer: 9 -->
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsQuestion_14">Two similar polygons have ratio of similitude k = 3. What is the ratio of their areas?</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsAnswerOne_14">3</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsAnswerTwo_14">9</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsAnswerThree_14">6</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsCorrectAnswer_14">9</string>

    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryWorkedExamples_14">• A hexagon is divided into 4 triangles with areas 6, 8, 5, and 7; total area = 6 + 8 + 5 + 7 = 26.
\n • Two similar triangles have sides in ratio k = 2; their areas are in ratio k² = 4. If the smaller has area 15, the larger has area 15 × 4 = 60.
\n • A convex quadrilateral has diagonals of length 8 and 6 meeting at angle 30°: area = ½ × 8 × 6 × sin 30° = ½ × 8 × 6 × ½ = 12.</string>

    <!-- Q: k=2, smaller area=15 — larger area? Answer: 60 -->
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryWorkedExQuestion_14">Two similar triangles have ratio of similitude k = 2. If the smaller triangle has area 15, what is the area of the larger triangle?</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryWorkedExAnswerOne_14">30</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryWorkedExAnswerTwo_14">45</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryWorkedExAnswerThree_14">60</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryWorkedExCorrectAnswer_14">60</string>

